title: @OspreyVB Sweeps Savannah State 3-0
text: registered the set-winning kill that allowed UNF to take a 2-0 lead in the match. The third set had another close start, but UNF eventually gained an eight-point, 16-8 advantage on a Desaulnay kill. Although Savannah State attempted to chip away at UNF's lead, the Ospreys scored three-consecutive points to end the set and take a 2-0 lead in the match. UNF begins a four-match homestand with a pair of matches this weekend. The Ospreys host Lipscomb on Friday at 6 p.m., and NJIT on Saturday at 1 p.m., at UNF Arena.
